<TcPlcObject Version="1.1.0.1" ProductVersion="3.1.4026.18">
  <POU Name="_README" Id="{e4c1d054-8b36-5c9b-4324-40fa89cc88fe}" SpecialFunc="None">
    <Declaration><![CDATA[// This function block exists for documentation only. Do not instantiate it.
FUNCTION_BLOCK _README
VAR
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
    <Implementation>
      <ST><![CDATA[
(*
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                  FANUC R-30iB Plus  –  TwinCAT EtherCAT Library             ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

  PURPOSE
  ───────
  Ready-made function blocks for controlling a FANUC R-30iB Plus robot over
  EtherCAT using the FANUC EtherCAT Slave option (R-30iB Plus, PDO3 mapping).
  Handles the full enable sequence, safety signal management, and program
  start in both RSR and PNS modes.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  LIBRARY CONTENTS
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Data types (DUTs\)
    ST_FanucStatus      Live robot status decoded from EtherCAT inputs
    ST_FanucControl     Robot control commands written to EtherCAT outputs
    E_FanucEnableState  State enum for the enable sequence state machine
    E_FanucStartMode    RSR or PNS program start mode selector

  Function blocks (POUs\)
    FB_FanucStatus      Reads aDI byte array → ST_FanucStatus
    FB_FanucControl     Writes ST_FanucControl → aDO byte array
    FB_FanucEnable      Enable sequence state machine + safety signal management
    FB_FanucStartProgram Program start in RSR or PNS mode with ACK detection

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  SIGNAL MAPPING  (FANUC PDO3)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  EtherCAT INPUTS  →  aDI (GVL_Fanuc.DI0)   Robot UO → PLC
  ┌────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Byte   │ Bit      │ Signal                                             │
  ├────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ aDI[0] │ 0        │ UO[1]  CMDENBL   – remote cmd enable confirmed     │
  │        │ 1        │ UO[2]  SYSRDY    – servo on, no alarm              │
  │        │ 2        │ UO[3]  PROGRUN   – program executing               │
  │        │ 3        │ UO[4]  PAUSED    – program paused                  │
  │        │ 4        │ UO[5]  HELD      – HOLD active                     │
  │        │ 5        │ UO[6]  FAULT     – alarm present                   │
  │        │ 6        │ UO[7]  ATPERCH   – robot at home position          │
  │        │ 7        │ UO[8]  TPENBL    – teach pendant switch ON         │
  ├────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ aDI[1] │ 0        │ UO[9]  BATALM    – battery alarm                   │
  │        │ 1        │ UO[10] BUSY      – controller busy                 │
  ├────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ aDI[2] │ 0..7     │ UO[11..18] ACK1..ACK8 (RSR) / SNO1..SNO8 (PNS)   │
  └────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  EtherCAT OUTPUTS  →  aDO (GVL_Fanuc.DO0)   PLC → Robot UI
  ┌────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Byte   │ Bit      │ Signal                                             │
  ├────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ aDO[0] │ 0        │ UI[1]  *IMSTP      NC – FALSE = emergency stop     │
  │        │ 1        │ UI[2]  *HOLD       NC – FALSE = pause robot        │
  │        │ 2        │ UI[3]  *SFSPD      NC – FALSE = safe-speed limit   │
  │        │ 3        │ UI[4]  CSTOPI         – pulse to abort cycle       │
  │        │ 4        │ UI[5]  FAULT_RESET    – pulse to clear alarms      │
  │        │ 5        │ UI[6]  START          – resume paused program      │
  │        │ 6        │ UI[7]  HOME           – macro use only             │
  │        │ 7        │ UI[8]  ENBL        NC – FALSE = disable motion     │
  ├────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ aDO[1] │ 0..7     │ UI[9..16] RSR1..RSR8 (RSR) / PNS1..PNS8 (PNS)    │
  ├────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ aDO[2] │ 1        │ UI[18] PROD_START  – triggers PNS execution        │
  └────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  NC = Normally Closed. These signals MUST be held TRUE for the robot to run.
  Dropping them to FALSE stops or limits the robot. This is the fail-safe
  wiring convention – a broken cable stops the robot rather than running it.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ENABLE SEQUENCE  (FB_FanucEnable)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Set bEnable to TRUE. The FB steps through these states automatically:

  1. SetInitConditions  Assert *IMSTP, *HOLD, *SFSPD and ENBL simultaneously.
  2. ClearFault         Pulse FAULT_RESET until bFault clears (5 s timeout → Error).
  3. CheckTP            Wait for TP switch to be OFF (bTP_Enabled = FALSE).
                        bTPWarning = TRUE while waiting – use for HMI indication.
  4. WaitReady          Wait for CMDENBL AND SYSRDY (5 s timeout → Error).
  5. Ready              bReady = TRUE. Monitors continuously for fault/TP changes.

  To reset after Error: set bEnable to FALSE, then TRUE again.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  PROGRAM START  (FB_FanucStartProgram)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  RSR mode  (eMode = E_FanucStartMode.RSR)
    Programs 1..8. Each maps to one RSR bit (UI[9..16]), pulsed for 200 ms.
    Robot acknowledges on UO[11..18] ACK bits → fbStart.bAck goes TRUE one scan.
    The FANUC controller must be configured for RSR mode.

  PNS mode  (eMode = E_FanucStartMode.PNS)
    Programs 1..255. Binary-encoded across UI[9..16] (PNS1..PNS8).
    PROD_START (UI[18]) is pulsed simultaneously for 200 ms to trigger execution.
    Robot acknowledges via PROGRUN rising edge → fbStart.bAck goes TRUE one scan.
    The FANUC controller must be configured for PNS mode.

  NOTE: RSR and PNS are mutually exclusive modes configured on the robot
  controller (not switchable at runtime from the PLC). Set eStartMode to match.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  MINIMUM MAIN TEMPLATE
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  // Declare in VAR:
  //   fbStatus  : FB_FanucStatus;
  //   fbControl : FB_FanucControl;
  //   fbEnable  : FB_FanucEnable;
  //   fbStart   : FB_FanucStartProgram;
  //   stStatus  : ST_FanucStatus;
  //   stControl : ST_FanucControl;

  // 1. Read status (always first)
  fbStatus(aDI := GVL_Fanuc.DI0, stStatus => stStatus);

  // 2. Run enable sequence
  fbEnable(
      bEnable    := bEnableRobot,
      stStatus   := stStatus,
      bExtIMSTP  := bExtIMSTP,   // Wire from NOT bSoftEStop
      bExtHold   := bExtHold,    // Wire from NOT bPauseButton
      bExtSFSPD  := bExtSFSPD,   // Wire from bFenceOK / area scanner
      bCycleStop := bCycleStop,  // Pulse to abort current cycle
      stControl  => stControl
  );

  // 3. Start a program (rising edge on bStartProgram, gated by bReady)
  fbStart(
      bStart    := bStartProgram,
      nProgram  := nProgram,
      eMode     := eStartMode,   // E_FanucStartMode.RSR or .PNS
      bReady    := fbEnable.bReady,
      stStatus  := stStatus,
      stControl := stControl);   // VAR_IN_OUT – stamps start bits in place

  // 4. Write outputs (always last)
  fbControl(aDO := GVL_Fanuc.DO0, stControl := stControl);

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  LIBRARY DESIGN NOTES
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  I/O injection
    The library contains no AT %I* or AT %Q* hardware-linked variables.
    The caller passes GVL_Fanuc.DI0 / DO0 at the call site (VAR_IN_OUT).
    This is required for TwinCAT library compatibility and allows the same
    FBs to be used with any EtherCAT slave address or PDO mapping.

  Default-reset pattern
    FB_FanucEnable zeroes all stControl outputs at the start of every scan,
    then re-asserts active signals. This prevents any output from getting
    stuck TRUE when the state machine changes state.

  Cycle_stop edge detection
    bCycleStop is edge-detected (R_TRIG) inside FB_FanucEnable. The caller
    can hold it TRUE without causing repeated cycle stops.

  Safety signal defaults
    bExtIMSTP, bExtHold and bExtSFSPD all default to TRUE. If left unwired,
    the FB operates safely in stand-alone mode. Wire them to your safety logic
    for a production system.
*)]]></ST>
    </Implementation>
    <LineIds Name="_README">
      <LineId Id="1" Count="141" />
    </LineIds>
</POU>
</TcPlcObject>
